#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:1
msgid "_display_new_figures"
msgstr "_display_new_figures"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:3
msgid "Firma"
msgstr "Signature"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:9
msgid "Che problema risolve"
msgstr "What problem it solves"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:11
msgid ""
"Mostra esplicitamente in IPython/Jupyter le figure create dopo un certo "
"snapshot iniziale, evitando che restino nascoste dentro un context "
"manager di stile."
msgstr "Explicitly shows in IPython/Jupyter the figures created after a given initial snapshot, preventing them from staying hidden inside a style context manager."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:13
msgid "Contratto sugli input"
msgstr "Input contract"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:15
msgid ""
"`existing_nums` deve contenere i numeri di figura presenti prima di "
"entrare nel blocco monitorato."
msgstr "`existing_nums` must contain the figure numbers present before entering the monitored block."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:16
msgid ""
"La funzione confronta questo insieme con `plt.get_fignums()` per "
"individuare solo le figure nuove."
msgstr "The function compares this set with `plt.get_fignums()` to identify only the new figures."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:17
msgid "Se `IPython.display` non e disponibile, la funzione non fa nulla."
msgstr "If `IPython.display` is not available, the function does nothing."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:19
msgid "Dove viene usata"
msgstr "Where it is used"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:21
msgid ""
"in [`_style_context`](style-context.md) quando l'esecuzione avviene in un"
" notebook IPython/Jupyter"
msgstr "in [`_style_context`](style-context.md) when execution happens inside an IPython/Jupyter notebook"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:23
msgid "Come fallisce"
msgstr "How it fails"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:25
msgid "In uso normale non alza eccezioni specifiche del package."
msgstr "In normal use it does not raise package-specific exceptions."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:26
msgid ""
"Se il supporto di display non e disponibile, la funzione si comporta come"
" un no-op."
msgstr "If display support is not available, the function behaves as a no-op."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:28
msgid "Perche resta privata"
msgstr "Why it remains private"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/display-new-figures.md:30
msgid ""
"Serve solo a rifinire l'integrazione notebook di `mespy`: non rappresenta"
" un'operazione autonoma utile per l'utente finale."
msgstr "It is only meant to refine `mespy`'s notebook integration: it does not represent an autonomous operation that is useful to end users."

